<1ST_LINE>r i PM-BRF--China-Pirates     06-07 0131</1ST_LINE>
<2ND_LINE>PM-BRF--China-Pirates,0134</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Pirates Reappear In East China Sea</HEAD>
<DATELINE>BEIJING (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Pirates are harassing boats off the eastern
seaboard of China for the first time since the Communists took over
the mainland in 1949, an official newspaper reported today.
   The China Daily said that in the past few weeks, pirates in the
East China Sea off the coast of Shanghai, Zhejiang province and
Fujian province have stolen the catches of fishing boats and
assaulted and kidnapped fishermen.
   The daily said the pirates have been armed with iron pipes,
explosives and detonators. It not say how many boats were involved
in pirating or indicate their origin.
   It did say, however, that six boats from a Fujian province county
had been seized in the past two months for illegal possession of
fish.
</TEXT>
