<DATELINE>WASHINGTON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Former President Ford says the deficit-saddled
federal budget process ``is in total shambles'' and Congress should
restore power to the White House to straighten out the mess.
   Ford called Monday for Congress to reinstate the president's
power to impound appropriated money, a device Congress removed when
it streamlined the budget process in 1974.
   ``The anti-impoundment provisions in my opinion have been a
disaster,'' Ford said in a speech at the National Press Club. The
