<HEAD>Dukakis Picks Up Bulk of Kentucky Delegation</HEAD>
<DATELINE>FRANKFORT, Ky. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Gov. Wallace Wilkinson of Kentucky endorsed
Democratic front-runner Michael Dukakis for the party's presidential
nomination and said almost all of the Kentucky delegation will
follow his lead.
   The switch means 41 delegates, most previously committed to Sen.
Albert Gore Jr. of Tennessee, will jump to the Dukakis camp. As it
now stands, all but six of Kentucky's 67 delegates to the July
convention will back the Massachusetts governor.
   The remaining delegates are committed to Jesse Jackson.
   Wilkinson, who had earlier pledged his support to Gore, said Gore
had not formally released him from that support but did not object
to the switch in allegiance.
