<TEXT>
   Former Sen. Gary Hart says he doesn't plan to run
for president in 1992, but says ``a lot can happen between now and
election time.''
   ``One candidate making a mistake can change the whole picture,''
the former Democratic candidate for the White House said.
   Hart, in London to promote a novel, said he prefers now to spend
his time writing books and practicing law.
   Commenting on the current presidential campaign, Hart said
Republican Vice President George Bush would make a mistake if he
were to ride President Reagan's popularity to the White House.
   ``Americans like independent leadership and Mr. Bush will not get
elected simply because of Ronald Reagan,'' he said.
