<HEAD>Airline Says Flight Attendants Have Slimmed Down</HEAD>
<NOTE>Eds: Stands as a writethru to a0507, recasting throughout to refer
to flight attendants sted stewardesses. No pickup.</NOTE>
<DATELINE>HARARE, Zimbabwe (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Air Zimbabwe's female flight attendants
have met a six-month deadline to lose weight, a newspaper reported
today.
   The Herald said flight attendants who were told in December to
trim down or face permanent grounding have met the ultimatum. It did
not say how many employees were involved.
   In issuing the order in December, the airline said its cabin
crews outweighed those of most other airlines.
   The Herald, which is published by government-owned Mass Media
Trust, today quoted an unidentified airline spokesman as saying the
flight attendants have lost weight. Airline officials today declined
to elaborate.
   Regulations set the minumum height for female flight attendants
at 5 feet 4 inches and require that they be proportionate in weight.
