<HEAD>Networks Plan Expanded Coverage of Primaries</HEAD>
<DATELINE>NEW YORK (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   ABC, NBC and CBS plan expanded coverage of
today's presidential primaries in California, New Jersey, New Mexico
and Montana.
   CBS will have one-minute updates at 8 p.m. and 11 p.m. and a
30-minute special at midnight EDT, Donna Dees, manager of
communications for CBS News, said Monday.
   ABC plans two-minute special reports at 8 p.m., after 9 p.m. and
after 10 p.m., with additional coverage around 11 p.m. EDT, said
Elise Adde, director of news information. The network's regularly
scheduled program ``Nightline,'' which airs at 11:30 p.m. EDT, will
run an hour instead of the normal 30 minutes, she said.
   Primary coverage at NBC will include two three-minute
interruptions at 8:56 p.m. and 10:15 p.m., with a 30-minute special
at 11:30 p.m. EDT, said Mark Angotti, an NBC researcher.
