<1ST_LINE>r p PM-SupremacistRally     06-07 0187</1ST_LINE>
<2ND_LINE>PM-Supremacist Rally,0190</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Georgia Governor Approves Capitol Rally For White Supremacists</HEAD>
<DATELINE>ATLANTA (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Georgia's governor, conceding white supremacists
have a right to rally, has granted the request of the Nationalist
Movement to gather on the state Capitol grounds the day before the
Democratic National Convention.
   ``There is no legal impediment to keep them from using the
Capitol grounds for their purposes,'' said Barbara Morgan, press
secretary to Gov. Joe Frank Harris. She said a letter to the group
was prepared Monday.
   The Nationalist Movement is based in Jackson, Miss., and is
afflilated with the Forsyth County Defense League, an organization
formed in the wake of civil rights activity in the county just north
of Atlanta.
   The city of Atlanta last month granted the Nationalist Movement a
parade permit to allow the group to parade from the Capitol to a
free-speech site near The Omni, where the Democratic convention will
be held July 18-21.
   Richard Barrett, a lawyer who heads the defense league, said he
expects 1,000 marchers. He said the group would be protected by its
own, unarmed security force _ youths in camouflage uniforms.
</TEXT>
