<2ND_LINE>AM-Hungary-Pilot,0114</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Pilot Returns to Hungary After Landing Glider in Romania `By
Mistake'</HEAD>
<DATELINE>BUDAPEST, Hungary (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A Hungarian pilot who landed his glider
in Romania after straying into Romanian airspace was returned to
Hungary, the official MTI news agency reported Tuesday.
   Ferenc Steinbinder landed his glider about 7.5 miles inside
Romanian territory near the town of Salonta on Saturday. MTI said he
made a navigational error.
   It said Steinbinder belongs to an aviation club of the Hungarian
army, but it didn't say if he was in the army.
   ``Following the usual legal formalities, the Romanian authorities
presented the glider and its pilot to the Hungarian authorities
Monday night,'' MTI said.
