<2ND_LINE>AM-BRF--China-Thief,0133</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Police Arrest Thief Who Put Victims to Sleep</HEAD>
<DATELINE>BEIJING (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Police in Shanghai arrested a man on suspicion of
stealing $5,400 after knocking his victims out with a powerful
sleeping powder.
   Police said Li Jiong, 46, from coastal Jiangsu province, carried
out 16 thefts in seven provinces since December after anesthetizing
people, the official Xinhua News Agency said Tuesday.
   One victim, a private businessman, said he was robbed of $119
after a man who shared a room with him in an inn invited him for a
drink and he instantly fell asleep. The drink was found to contain a
strong sleeping powder, police said.
   Another victim in Zhengzhou, Henan province, was robbed of
$2,405, police said.
   They said Li had past convictions for robbery and fraud.
