<DATELINE>WASHINGTON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Reported incidents of violence and harassment
aimed at homosexuals rose 42 percent last year, according to a study
released today which blamed an AIDS backlash as contributing to the
increase.
   A record 7,008 incidents, ranging from verbal abuse to murder,
were reported in 1987 to the National Gay and Lesbian Task Force,
according to Kevin Berrill, director of the task force's
Anti-violence Project.
   The statistics were compiled in the report ``Anti-Gay Violence,
Victimization & Defamation in 1987,'' the third such study by the
advocacy group.
