<1ST_LINE>r f BC-ResortsInternational     06-07 0188</1ST_LINE>
<2ND_LINE>BC-Resorts International,0197</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Griffin Begins Tender Offer</HEAD>
<DATELINE>NEW YORK (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Merv Griffin began a tender offer Tuesday for
Class A shares of Resorts International Inc., the casino company he
is splitting up with developer Donald Trump.
   The offer, being made by Griffco Acquisition Corp., will pay
shareholders $36 a share and expires at midnight EDT July 5.
   Griffin, the TV talk-show host turned investor, will pay
approximately $300 million for the Atlantic City, N.J., company,
which is controlled by Trump.
   Using his profits from the deal and other funds, Trump will buy
back the company's unfinished crown jewel, the vast Taj Mahal casino
in Atlantic City, for $230 million.
   The agreement calls for Trump, Resorts' chairman, to get a total
of $160 million _ $135 a share, or about $100 million _ for his
Class B shares, and $60 million to terminate his management
contract. The Class B shares, which carry special voting rights,
give him 88 percent control of the company.
   Griffin first offered to buy Resorts on March 17 for $35 a share.
The tender offer culminates a long series of on-again, off-again
negotiations.
</TEXT>
