<HEAD>Joseph Gallo Elected Wine Institute Chief</HEAD>
<DATELINE>SAN FRANCISCO (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Joseph Gallo has been elected chairman of
the Wine Institute, becoming the third member of his family to head
the trade group.
   Gallo, 47, vice president of Modesto's E. & J. Gallo Winery, was
elected at the institute's annual meeting on Monday.
   His father, Ernest, was chairman in 1954-55 and again in 1957-58.
His cousin, Robert, was chairman in 1977-1978.
   John De Luca continues as Wine Institute president.
   Gallo predicted a 50 percent increase in wine exports for the
year, compared to a 65 percent increase last year. He said
first-quarter exports of California wine reached 3.8 million
gallons, up 94 percent from a year ago. Canada led first quarter
export with shipments of more than a million gallons, more than
double last year's level.
</TEXT>
