<DATELINE>NEW YORK (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   The stock market declined slightly today, running
into resistance from sellers after its sharp rally over the past
week.
   The Dow Jones average of 30 industrials, up more than 118 points
over the past five sessions, dropped 5.69 to 2,069.52 by noontime
today on Wall Street
   Losers outnumbered gainers by about 7 to 6 in the overall tally
of New York Stock Exchange-listed issues, with 595 up, 712 down and
519 unchanged.
   Interest rates rose in the bond market today. Prices of long-term
government bonds, which move in the opposite direction from interest
rates, fell about $5 for each $1,000 in face value.
   Analysts said the pressure on bonds stemmed largely from
inflation worries that have increased with rising commodity prices
of late.
   Brokers said uncertainties over inflation and interest-rate
prospects helped to discourage traders from chasing after stocks
with the popular averages near the high end of the trading range in
which they have fluctuated for the past several months.
   Some computer and semiconductor issues gained ground. Digital
Equipment rose 1| to 109}; International Business Machines ] to
114}; Motorola ] to 50[ and Hewlett-Packard { to 57].
   Egghead Inc. traded at 18} on heavy volume in the
over-the-counter market after an initial public offering of 3.6
million shares of the computer software retailer's stock at $17.
   Among other OTC technology issues, Sun Microsystems gained 1] to
37|; Micron Technology } to 23\, and Lotus Development { to 23{.
   The NYSE's composite index of all its listed common stocks lost
.17 to 150.38. At the American Stock Exchange, the market value
index was up .50 at 302.44.
   Volume on the Big Board came to 80.03 million shares at noontime,
against 83.37 million at the same point Monday.
